'''''Polyhedron''''' was originally a publication of [[TSR, Inc.]]'s [[Wikipedia:RPGA|Role Playing Game Association (RPGA)]] that sometimes included articles concerning [[West End Games]] ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''. Following the RPGA's acquisition by [[Wizards of the Coast]], it became a publication dedicated to [[Wikipedia:D20 System|d20 system]] games such as Wizards of the Coast's ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''. In all of these incarnations, the publication provided missions, game statistics and background material for gamers.

In [[2002]], ''Polyhedron'' became a section of [[Wikipedia:Dungeon (magazine)|''Dungeon'' magazine]]. It continued to run until [[August]] [[2004]], when ''Dungeon'' editor Erik Mona discontinued ''Polyhedron'' and refocused the magazine purely on Dungeons and Dragons content.

Within the continuity of [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]], issues from the single issues of Polyhedron are [[Canon|non-canon]] but may contain ambiguously canon elements, while issues printed after the merger with ''Dungeon'' are canon. 

Despite originating prior to April 2003, and being deemed "unofficial" by [[Leland Chee]],<ref name="SWB">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=222689&start=1575#14229569|thread=Welcome some BCaT VIPs|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2006-02-28|time=6:28 PM}}</ref> the planets [[Mandrine/Legends|Mandrine]]<ref name="P591991" /> and [[Shar'Ack]]<ref name="P591991" /> were included in [[2009]]'s ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''.<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> [[Mandrine]] later became [[canon]] with its inclusion in [[2018]]'s ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story: Tales from Vandor]]'' by [[Jason Fry]].<ref name="SASWSTfV">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story: Tales from Vandor]]''</ref>

